{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"jQuery","mdn_url":"/fr/docs/Glossary/jQuery","locale":"fr","native":"Français","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p><strong>jQuery</strong> est une <a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"Cette documentation n'a pas encore été rédigée, vous pouvez aider en contribuant&nbsp;!\">bibliothèque</a> <a href=\"/fr/docs/Glossary/JavaScript\">JavaScript</a> qui se concentre sur la simplification de la manipulation de <a href=\"/fr/docs/Glossary/DOM\">DOM</a>, les appels d'<a href=\"/fr/docs/Glossary/AJAX\">AJAX</a> et la gestion des <a href=\"/fr/docs/Glossary/event\">évènements</a>. Elle est fréquemment utilisée par les développeurs JavaScript.</p>\n<p>jQuery utilise un format, <code>$(selector).action()</code> pour assigner un (ou plusieurs) élément à un évènement. Pour expliquer cela en détail, <code>$(selector)</code> appelle jQuery pour sélectionner un élément <code>selector</code> et l'affecte à un évènement d'<a href=\"/fr/docs/Glossary/API\">API</a> appelé <code>.action()</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token function\">$</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>document<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">ready</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">alert</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Hello World!\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">$</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"#blackBox\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">hide</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Le code ci-dessus remplit la même fonction que le code suivant :</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>window<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function-variable function\">onload</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">alert</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Hello World!\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getElementById</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"blackBox\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>style<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>display <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"none\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"télécharger_jquery","title":"Télécharger jQuery","isH3":false,"content":"<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th><strong>npm</strong></th>\n      <th>bower (solo file)</th>\n      <th>Google CDN</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td><code>npm install jquery</code></td>\n      <td><code>bower install https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.2.1.min.js</code></td>\n      <td><code>https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.2.1/jquery.min.js</code></td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"en_apprendre_plus","title":"En apprendre plus","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"culture_générale","title":"Culture générale","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a title=\"jQuery\" href=\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/JQuery\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">jQuery</a> sur Wikipedia</li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://jquery.com/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">jQuery Official Website</a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"apprentissage_de_jquery","title":"Apprentissage de jQuery","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.codecademy.com/learn/jquery\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Le cours en ligne sur codecademy.com</a> (en)</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"information_technique","title":"Information technique","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://api.jquery.com/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Documentation de référence de l'API</a> (en)</li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Télécharger jQuery","id":"télécharger_jquery"},{"text":"En apprendre plus","id":"en_apprendre_plus"}],"summary":"jQuery est une bibliothèque JavaScript qui se concentre sur la simplification de la manipulation de DOM, les appels d'AJAX et la gestion des évènements. Elle est fréquemment utilisée par les développeurs JavaScript.","popularity":0.0003,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"jQuery","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"jQuery","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"jQuery","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"jQuery","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"jQuery","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"jQuery","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"jQuery","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"jQuery","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"folder":"fr/glossary/jquery","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/fr/glossary/jquery/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/fr/docs/Glossary","title":"Glossaire MDN : définitions des termes du Web"},{"uri":"/fr/docs/Glossary/jQuery","title":"jQuery"}],"pageTitle":"jQuery - Glossaire MDN : définitions des termes du Web | MDN","noIndexing":false}}